external_knowledge:
- "Spiritual practices" may include activities such as meditation, prayer, or attending religious services, which are believed to promote emotional and mental wellbeing; 
- "Wellbeing" refers to a person's overall quality of life, including their physical, emotional, and mental health; 
- "Frequency of practice" indicates how often an individual engages in spiritual activities, which can influence their perceived wellbeing; 
- "Trends" in this context signify patterns or changes in spiritual practices and wellbeing scores over time and across different regions.

sql:
SELECT frequency_name, COUNT(frequency_id) AS frequency_count
FROM frequencies
GROUP BY frequency_name;

SELECT MAX(trend_value) AS max_trend_value
FROM trends
WHERE year = 2020;
